# boot/config.txt.patch
#
# Lines to APPEND to /boot/config.txt on the Pi.
# bootstrap.sh detects the sentinel "# --- begin bt2iap ---" before appending
# so this block is safe to apply multiple times (idempotent).
#
# Purpose: enable dwc2, the USB On-The-Go / gadget-mode driver for the
# Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W. Without this overlay the Pi enumerates its USB
# port in host mode and the ipod-gadget kernel modules will not load.
#
# Reference: CLAUDE.md § "USB role" — gadget/device mode via dwc2
#   dtoverlay=dwc2 must appear in /boot/config.txt
#   modules-load=dwc2 must follow rootwait in /boot/cmdline.txt
#
# Do NOT add this to a Pi 4/5 — those use a different USB controller.
# Verified target: Pi Zero 2 W running Raspberry Pi OS Lite 64-bit.

# --- begin bt2iap ---
# Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W USB gadget support for iPod emulation (bt2iap)
dtoverlay=dwc2
# --- end bt2iap ---
